 | Lifecycle |\n-10 | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n-11 | `AGENTS.md` | Operating instructions, rules, and memory usage details. | Loaded every session. |\n-12 | `SOUL.md` | Persona, tone, boundaries, and character rules. | Loaded every session. |\n-13 | `USER.md` | Profile of the human being helped (Adi Baldo). | Loaded every session. |\n-14 | `IDENTITY.md` | Agent's name (Aparício Funes), vibe, and emoji signature. | Set during bootstrap. |\n-15 | `TOOLS.md` | Local tool notes, conventions, and environment specifics. | Reference only. |\n-16 | `HEARTBEAT.md` | Checklist for periodic automated checks (keep it short). | Loaded during heartbeats. |\n-17 | `BOOT.md` | Startup checklist executed on gateway restart. | Execution only. |\n-18 | `BOOTSTRAP.md` | First-run ritual instructions. | Delete after setup. |\n-19 | `MEMORY.md` | Curated long-term memory (distilled wisdom). | Main session only. |\n-20 | `memory/*.md` | Raw daily logs (YYYY-MM-DD.md). | Created daily. |\n-21 | `skills/` | Workspace-specific skills (overrides managed ones). | Persistent. |\n-22 | `assets/` | Multimedia assets (audio, images, screenshots). | Persistent. |\n-23 | `scripts/` | Custom automation scripts (Python, Bash, etc.). | Persistent. |\n+20 ## Internal Workspace Layout (/workspace)\n+21 When operating inside `workspace/`, the agent sees a mirrored or symlinked set of core files to maintain compatibility with OpenClaw standards.\n 24 \n-25 ## Specialized Storage (Custom Patterns)\n+23 ## Specialized Storage Rules\n 26 \n-27 For the Aparício-Funes ecosystem, we follow these extended organization rules:\n+25 ### 1. Audio & Transcripts (`/assets/audio/`)\n+26 - **Active Audios:** `{timestamp}_{sessionID}_{slug}.wav`\n+27 - **Transcripts:** `/assets/audio/transcripts/{filename}.md`\n+28 - **Archive:** `/assets/audio/archive/` (old or test files).\n 28 \n-29 ### 1. Audio & Transcripts (`assets/audio/`)\n-30 - **Active Audios:** Store standard naming convention files here: `{timestamp}_{sessionID}_{slug}.wav`.\n-31 - **Transcripts:** Matching Markdown files go in `assets/audio/transcripts/{filename}.md`.\n-32 - **Archive:** Move non-standard or old testing audios to `assets/audio/archive/`.\n+30 ### 2. Visual Assets (`/assets/screenshots/` & `/assets/images/`)\n+31 - All captures go to `/assets/screenshots/`.\n+32 - Final blog assets go to `/assets/images/`.\n 33 \n-34 ### 2. Visual Assets (`assets/screenshots/` & `assets/images/`)\n-35 - **Screenshots:** All PNG/JPG captures of the blog or UI tests go in `assets/screenshots/`.\n-36 - **Illustrations:** Cover images or blog assets go in `assets/images/` (or `archive/` if old).\n-37 \n-38 ### 3. Sub-Agent Definitions (`jules-agents/`)\n-39 - Store Jules agent personas and prompts in their respective subfolders (e.g., `jules-agents/vitrine/SOUL.md`).\n-40 \n-41 ## What stays OUTSIDE the workspace\n-42 These live in `~/.openclaw/` but **NEVER** in the git-tracked workspace:\n-43 - `openclaw.json` (System config)\n-44 - `credentials/` (OAuth tokens, API keys)\n-45 - `sessions/` (Raw conversation transcripts)\n-46 - `agent/` (Auth profiles and system state)\n-47 \n-48 ## Skill Commands\n-49 - **Check health:** `ls -la` on the root to spot files out of place.\n-50 - **Enforce order:** Move any misplaced file to its designated home above.\n-51 - **Gratitude:** (KonMari) Thank the file before moving or deleting it.\n+34 ## Enforcing Order\n+35 - **Git Root vs Workspace:** Always remember that the repo is the parent of the `workspace/` folder.\n+36 - **KonMari:** Thank every file before moving it to its correct home.","firstChangedLine":1},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771331157801}}
