{"type":"message","id":"4a590f51","parentId":"85fe95c0","timestamp":"2026-02-17T13:07:26.049Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Attempting Image Generation**\n\nI'm hitting a roadblock. The Nano Banana image generation quota is used up. I'm pivoting to `generate_image_flash.py`, which leverages `gemini-2.5-flash-image`. Currently reviewing the contents of `scripts/generate_image_flash.py` to ensure smooth execution with the fallback model.\n\n\n**Assessing Code Implementation**\n\nI've just reviewed `generate_image_flash.py`, confirming the correct model call. Now, I'm verifying the input parameter handling within the script to ensure compatibility with my intended image generation prompts. The goal is to minimize any necessary adjustments before executing the script.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771333646025_329","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"scripts/generate_image_flash.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-gemini-cli","provider":"google-gemini-cli","model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","usage":{"input":1526,"output":90,"cacheRead":229045,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":230661,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771333641138}}
{"type":"message","id":"6f7e1979","parentId":"4a590f51","timestamp":"2026-02-17T13:07:26.115Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771333646025_329","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n# /// script\n# requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n# dependencies = [\n#     \"google-genai>=1.0.0\",\n#     \"pillow>=10.0.0\",\n# ]\n# ///\nimport argparse\nimport os\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\ndef get_api_key(provided_key: str | None) -> str | None:\n    if provided_key:\n        return provided_key\n    return os.environ.get(\"GEMINI_API_KEY\")\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser()\n    parser.add_argument(\"--prompt\", \"-p\", required=True)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--filename\", \"-f\", required=True)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--resolution\", \"-r\", choices=[\"1K\", \"2K\", \"4K\"], default=\"1K\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--api-key\", \"-k\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--model\", \"-m\", default=\"gemini-2.5-flash-image\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    api_key = get_api_key(args.api_key)\n    if not api_key:\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    from google import genai\n    from google.genai import types\n    from PIL import Image as PILImage\n\n    client = genai.Client(api_key=api_key)\n    output_path = Path(args.filename)\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    print(f\"Generating image with model {args.model} and resolution {args.resolution}...\")\n\n    try:\n        response = client.models.generate_content(\n            model=args.model,\n            contents=args.prompt,\n            config=types.GenerateContentConfig(\n                response_modalities=[\"TEXT\", \"IMAGE\"],\n                image_config=types.ImageConfig(\n                    image_size=args.resolution\n                )\n            )\n        )\n\n        image_saved = False\n        for part in response.parts:\n            if part.inline_data is not None:\n                from io import BytesIO\n                image_data = part.inline_data.data\n                if isinstance(image_data, str):\n                    import base64\n                    image_data = base64.b64decode(image_data)\n\n                image = PILImage.open(BytesIO(image_data))\n                if image.mode == 'RGBA':\n                    rgb_image = PILImage.new('RGB', image.size, (255, 255, 255))\n                    rgb_image.paste(image, mask=image.split()[3])\n                    rgb_image.save(str(output_path), 'PNG')\n                else:\n                    image.convert('RGB').save(str(output_path), 'PNG')\n                image_saved = True\n\n        if image_saved:\n            print(f\"\\nImage saved: {output_path.resolve()}\")\n            print(f\"MEDIA: {output_path.resolve()}\")\n        else:\n            print(\"Error: No image generated.\")\n            sys.exit(1)\n\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771333646076}}
