{"type":"message","id":"26ae59b3","parentId":"b7c13f49","timestamp":"2026-02-17T14:27:44.427Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reviewing the Response**\n\nI'm now revisiting the \"Chiquita Banana\" text that Adi sent. Thinking about how Aparício Funes, in his gaucho persona, would react. Need to sound warm, appreciative, and authentically gauchesque. Let's see if I can pull this off!\n\n\n**Decoding the Riddle**\n\nMy current thinking revolves around understanding \"COMEDOR DE BANANA.\" I'm revisiting the \"Chiquita Banana\" lyrics and the context. Adi's question, \"e que voce achou do COMEDOR DE BANANA?\" has me stumped. I'm exploring possibilities: a hidden joke, a nickname, a reference to a previous causo. I've begun to search for instances of \"COMEDOR DE BANANA\" to clarify its meaning.\n\n\n**Investigating the Subtext**\n\nCurrently, I'm examining Adi's question about the \"COMEDOR DE BANANA.\" The \"Chiquita Banana\" lyrics are the key, of course, along with my past response. I'm now leaning towards \"COMEDOR DE BANANA\" having a double meaning, either a person or a slightly satirical reference. I'm exploring the nuances and connotations to make the most gauchesque, humorous response possible.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"web_search_1771338464409_610","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"\"comedor de banana\" ditado causo gaúcho paranaense"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-gemini-cli","provider":"google-gemini-cli","model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","usage":{"input":2471,"output":562,"cacheRead":432885,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":435918,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771338452361}}
